# CODEOWNERS for Purview-as-Code (contoso-lab)
#
# GitHub enforces CODEOWNERS as required reviewers on matching paths when branch
# protection has "Require review from Code Owners" enabled. See:
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-security/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Format: <path glob>    <@owner1> [@owner2 ...]
# Later entries override earlier ones. Keep the catch-all first, then narrow.

# Catch-all — every PR needs at least one review from the repo owner.
*                                       @OWNER-PLACEHOLDER

# Control plane (Azure) — any Bicep change needs infra review.
/infra/                                 @OWNER-PLACEHOLDER

# Data plane (Purview catalog + M365 compliance YAML) — destructive diffs gate here.
/data-plane/                            @OWNER-PLACEHOLDER

# Automation scripts — REST API helpers and deploy logic.
/scripts/                               @OWNER-PLACEHOLDER

# CI/CD — workflow changes affect every plane.
/.github/workflows/                     @OWNER-PLACEHOLDER

# Owner-gated runtime workflows — explicit pin so a future broad change to
# CODEOWNERS cannot accidentally widen the reviewer set. The kv-temp-unlock
# workflow temporarily opens the lab Key Vault; only the lab owner may
# modify its dispatch surface or unlock logic.
/.github/workflows/kv-temp-unlock.yml   @OWNER-PLACEHOLDER

# Copilot / agent customization surface — changes here govern every future PR.
/.github/copilot-instructions.md        @OWNER-PLACEHOLDER
/.github/instructions/                  @OWNER-PLACEHOLDER
/.github/prompts/                       @OWNER-PLACEHOLDER
/.github/agents/                        @OWNER-PLACEHOLDER
/AGENTS.md                              @OWNER-PLACEHOLDER

# Architecture Decision Records — deliberate extra scrutiny.
/docs/adr/                              @OWNER-PLACEHOLDER
